AppiumIntro&DownloadInstall2

------------------------------------
Prerequisite to use APPIUM (Windows)
-------------------------------------
Pre-requisites:-----
Install Java (JDK)
Eclipse
Maven plugin for Eclipse
TestNG plugin for Eclipse
Selenium Standalone Server

Android Tools:-----
Android Studio
Appium Server/Appium Desktop
Appium Client Library1 Â  

*SET JAVA FIRST
1. Download JDK JAVA - .exe File 
2. Install & Check-In Program Files (Copy The Location)
3. Go To Advanced System Setting 'This PC'
4. Select Environment Variable -> System Variable -> Set Path 'JAVA_HOME'
5. Download Android STUDIO -> Official Page 
6. Install & Copy The SDK Path (C:\Users\Karan\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk)

*OPEN ANDROID STUDIO & CONFIGURE EMULATOR
1. Install & start the Appium server via Node.js 
-Download Node - Official website for Windows 
-Install & Finish 
-It will automatically install some other Tools For Node using Powershell 

*SET (ANDROID SDK & NODE) HOME PATH IN WINDOWS SYSTEM VARIABLES
-Check where is SDK Installed
-Copy the Path (C:\Users\Karan\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk)
-Open Environments Variables -> System Variables -> Paste AS 'ANDROID_HOME'













